<paragraph blockId="27.[213,333,1108,1132]" box="[213,333,1108,1132]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1061">
<emphasis box="[213,333,1108,1132]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1061">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[213,1170,1148,1204]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1061">
The specific name is derived from the Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[774,828,1149,1172]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1061">imag</emphasis>
-, meaning similar, referring to the similarity of this species to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meyrick)" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[560,825,1180,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Helcystogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="1061" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicuneum">
<emphasis box="[560,582,1181,1204]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1061">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[598,702,1180,1204]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1061">bicuneum</emphasis>
(Meyrick)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
